##Three days on the road, two days in Hong Lake, a diary of a visit from a native of Hubei Province

Editor's Note: This is the third submission conch has received. The author, Yifan, was unaware of the spread of the virus in Hubei Province when she set off on a trip home to visit her family. At that time, the media only mentioned Wuhan, and she did not have to go through Wuhan to drive herself back to Hong Lake from Guangzhou, so everyone thinks it's okay. Even after arriving in Hong Lake, there was no sense of the severity of the situation, and the family continued to make preparations for the new year as usual. Until the New Year's eve atmosphere suddenly tense, a family rushed to attack, finally returned to their home. If they had known about the virus, about how widespread it was, they never would have risked going home. They are a microcosm of the tens of thousands of Hupeis who returned to visit their families in Hubei and left before sealing off the city. Panic, confusion, anxiety, insecurity, this is their true psychological portrayal. So we know it is not them who are to blame, but the opacity of the information that has put them in this position.

At that time, the media only mentioned Wuhan, and she did not have to go through Wuhan to drive herself back to Hong Lake from Guangzhou, so everyone thinks it's okay. Until the New Year's eve atmosphere suddenly tense, a family rushed to attack, finally returned to their home. They are a microcosm of the tens of thousands of Hupeis who returned to visit their families in Hubei and left before sealing off the city. Panic, confusion, anxiety, insecurity, this is their true psychological portrayal. So we know it is not them who are to blame, but the opacity of the information that has put them in this position.

Diary of a native of Hubei Province

Yifan

Before we go,
Toward the end of 2019, relatives in Xiaogan, Hubei Province, asked if we would return home for the Spring Festival in 2020, and I didn't respond as quickly as usual.

Originally planned 2020 Spring Festival in Guangzhou with parents.

These years from Guangzhou back home for the Spring Festival, self-driving run for almost 10 years. In Hong Lake, the mother-in-law in Xiaogan, Honghu Xiaogan each spring festival run, high-speed rail tickets are difficult to grab, dragging large and small luggage, but also take a child transfer is not convenient, so a family of three driving home for the New Year is relatively the best choice. It takes two days to travel 1,000 km each way. It's cold, traffic, backache, food and sleep -- I don't feel like it this year, or travel abroad.

But January 23,2020 is the anniversary of his father-in-law's death, according to the rules of his hometown need to go back to worship. Husband said: "You really do not want to go back, I go back, and then you two go abroad together? " I thought about it, feel wrong, after all, the parents-in-law was very good to us, the sacrifice of the time not to go back, this is unfilial; It is not good for her husband to go home alone for a week; Xiaogan's mother and father are still waiting for us. The four-day round trip is hard, but think about it... UGH! Forget it, a clenched teeth, or back!

We're scheduled to leave at noon on January 21st. The specific itinerary is: 22 to Hong Lake, 23 to her parents-in-law grave, 24 to Xiaogan over the New Year's Eve, the fifth day back to Guangzhou. Once a decision has been made, the hardship of the journey and the unhappiness of cancelling the trip will soon be replaced by the joy of being reunited with loved ones. My husband and I began to prepare to go home as usual new year's, winter clothes stuffed with two large suitcases.

22 January
In fact, as early as around New Year's Day, I do not know where I heard about the SARS in Wuhan, but soon officially denied the official, and then deal with the "rumors" of the news, I quickly forgot about it. By January 18th, saw a message forwarded on WECHAT: "SARS in Wuhan has spread abroad, Hong Kong, Japan and Thailand have found. ". Several airports in the United States have increased / strengthened security checks for passengers in Wuhan. "My husband's nephew is studying for his doctorate in the United States, he did not believe it. He specially went to the World Health Organization website to see the latest news. He was convinced that the three cases spread abroad were all "Wuhan's virus, " as were those in Japan, and that "none of them had ever been to that seafood market. " So "you should be careful when you pass by Wuhan" . Our route was not through Wuhan, and family members discussed it on Wechat, saying it shouldn't matter if we were careful.

Information on the World Health Organization website, 18 January

Although on the evening news on January 20, Academician Zhong Nanshan stated that there was a "human-to-human transmission" in the COVID-19, we saw the news on the 21st. There was a new announcement that the virus was contagious, but we didn't realize how serious it was, or that the vast majority of people didn't know what was going on on the 21st. My other two colleagues and their families are also on the 20th, 21st according to the plan to drive back home. On the afternoon of the 20th, we busied ourselves tidying up the house, cleaning the refrigerator, buying food and beverages, and preparing snacks such as fruit and melon seeds for the road.
It's rare to get home without traffic

On January 21, we set off at noon. The road was not so blocked as we had imagined. It was about the end of the peak of Xiaonian's homecoming. This was the first time in many years that we encountered a relatively smooth homecoming. We also felt very lucky.

Check in at 9:00 p.m. At noon on the 22nd, he arrived at the home of his sister-in-law, a surgeon at a Hong Lake Hospital, in their new one-year-old house in the neighborhood next to the hospital.

The joy of returning home was quickly diluted by the information about the epidemic online, and with all the rumors, all the data, all the wechat videos, everyone's attention was drawn to one thing: the COVID-19 epidemic is starting to spread rapidly. Panic is creeping into my heart. We lived through SARS in 2003, when I was a phd student in Beijing and the campus was closed for two months. That familiar feeling was awakened, this time, I actually in the epidemic area, this is what luck?

Unfortunately, MY SISTER-IN-LAW IS SICK! She had to welcome her brothers back home and clean up when Khan caught a cold and was hoarse and coughing! Cough, fever, that's a symptom of a COVID-19 infection. To be on the safe side, my sister followed her husband to the hospital for a checkup. After a long time did not return, everyone in the home more anxious as if the hospital is now the most dangerous place, who knows good people can be infected in the hospital? Fortunately, the test result is a bacterial infection, just take medicine to rest. The heart hanging down a little.

January 23rd
The next day the epidemic took place on a major change, a landmark event is the 23rd at 10:00 am starting the city of Wuhan closed! The news came as a shock. My heart was clouded. Hong Lake was still a long way from Wuhan, but the outbreaks in Huanggang and Ezhou were worsening. Send text messages to relatives in Wuhan, who are rarely in touch with each other. This is when they most need your attention. Their reply is still very optimistic, all the relatives in Wuhan are healthy and safe. Call Xiaogan's father and tell them to wear a mask when they go out. Dad said, "I know, older people are more susceptible to infection. Your mother is very concerned about the epidemic and watches the news in front of the TV every day. "

The grave visit was the most important event of the trip back home. On the morning of the 23rd, my family, my brother-in-law's family and my brother-in-law (my sister was sick and resting at home) drove themselves to the graves of my in-laws. The cemetery was about half an hour away from downtown Hong Lake. The Sky was overcast and drizzly and cold. Everyone was wearing masks and in a particularly gloomy mood. The cemetery was deserted and desolate, the ground overgrown with weeds and fallen leaves, and the censer filled with icy water. Second brother pulled out the weeds in front of the tomb with his hands, and simply tidied up the Leaf Storm. Everyone burned paper and incense, and covered a plastic bag on the bluestone slab to cushion it, kowtowing and kneeling. No firecrackers. In the light rain, everyone was silent.

Back home, I do not have the heart to watch TV, chat, hand has been holding the phone, brush about the new coronary pneumonia of all kinds of news. "have there been any confirmed cases in Hong Lake? " I asked my brother-in-law, who works at the hospital. "There are actually 33 suspected cases, and only two have been reported. "

College friends circle everyone began to ask each other, who is in Wuhan, the situation? Huanggang, Ezhou and seven other cities have been closed off, so fast that it's hard to react. Qianjiang, a long way from Wuhan, is closed, but Xiaogan, next to Wuhan, has not moved yet. In the evening, the second sister suddenly sent a screen shot to me, is about Xiaogan to seal the city of "inside information. ". Friends circle before this spread "gossip" one by one quickly become a fact, I judge the screenshot for the real possibility is very high, maybe Xiaogan really should be closed! But Will it be tomorrow? My sister also told me that one of her colleagues couldn't come from Hanchuan. Maybe it's just that Hanchuan can't leave town?

Do you want to go to Xiaogan tomorrow? Well, that's GONNA have to change. I began to make false, but still struggling to retain a trace of fantasy: Maybe Xiaogan is okay? We'll go to Xiaogan tomorrow for a New Year's Eve, stay at mom and dad's for one night and then go back to Guangzhou on the 1st day?

We planned to return to Xiaogan for the New Year on the 24th. Brother a week ago has been the New Year's Eve and the second day of the recipe is designed, but also specifically sent me "look" , said and sister-in-law is ready, sister-in-law's cooking is first-class. But this younger brother is also going to show off, special study and try to do a steamed meat, very successful! He also sent a steaming photo of the Tamales, saying he was just waiting for us to get back to his cooking. The younger brother's family is going to take mom and dad over for New Year's Eve dinner this year. It will be the first time for our family to celebrate the New Year at the younger brother's home in so many years. Hong Lake is just one hundred and thirty km from Xiaogan, less than three hours away, and our family is expecting us.

24 January
Early on the morning of the 24th,. Are we going or not? Everyone has no idea, the husband's meaning is not to Xiaogan, too dangerous. My boss is not happy: in front of the home, only more than 100 kilometers! But I knew in my heart that the number of people infected with Xiaogan was increasing. It was bad. It was safest not to go to Xiaogan at this time.

Brother 8:00 on Wechat urged me: "Did you go? "
I hesitantly replied: "Xiaogan may want to seal off the city, we dare not go AH. "
The younger brother is anxious: "where so coincidental? Today closes a city? Today but is the New Year 30! "
I said, "If we do, we won't be able to go back to Guangzhou. "
The younger brother is a little unhappy: "It's not so scary! You come over to have dinner with your parents today, and then go the next day, ok? "

I know he prepared the New Year's Eve dinner, in large part also to entertain me, the third sister back from afar. Well, can I not understand his intentions? I have some vacillation, still go to filial piety to see parents? There's nothing to be said for a meal..

The younger brother somewhat disheartened ground continues to concede: "If can not, you hurriedly drive to come over, arrive I immediately start to eat! "! After dinner, you're going back to Hong Lake! Hong Lake is far from Wuhan. It should be safe. Hong Lake to Xiaogan round trip about six hours, hard brother-in-law a trip! What?"

I really can not bear, said: "or... We gamble? Xiaogan will not seal today? "
At this time I heard my brother-in-law vaguely advised: "Don't say... "
Brother finally tone dim: "never mind, DO NOT GAMBLE! You do not return to do not return. "
After the discussion, I put down the phone, as if I saw, my brother in the kitchen in the face of a pile of semi-finished New Year's Eve meal, that disappointed expression. I feel like I'm 130 miles from home, waiting for us.

Call Dad and explain that we're not coming back. Dad is very sensible, immediately loudly said: "Do not return, safety first! TOMORROW YOU HURRY BACK TO GUANGZHOU! "

At 11 a.m. , it was announced that Xiaogan's public transportation had been suspended. Then Xiaogan will be 24 at 24:00 on the news of the city also announced. Fortunately, we finally decided not to see parents and younger brother Xiaogan, or will be sealed in Xiaogan can not go home, will also increase the burden of relatives. I'm still a little freaked out about it.

That's the truth. I can't go back to my parents'house for New Year's.

In that case, spend the next thirty years in Hong Lake and go back to Guangzhou in the morning! It feels like the footsteps of a terrible invisible demon... have begun to creep up on us... leaving us no time to lose.

My brother-in-law and his family are ready to go back to Jingzhou... to see us stay... and suddenly decide... to stay in Hong Lake for the 30s... and go back to Jingzhou in the morning! This decision, let her husband's brother-in-law suddenly happy to feel like "this 30, lively Ha! " See her husband's smiling face, we suddenly rose a happy new year's reunion.

After two days of taking the medicine, my sister felt refreshed and could make a sound in her throat. She will go to the country mother-in-law's house, one is to visit the elderly (she used to go back to her in-laws in the New Year's Eve dinner) , send gifts; The second is to take some fresh vegetables from the countryside to stock up for the New Year. (few restaurants are open from the first to the third day.). She asked if we would like to pick some farm fresh vegetables together? Yeah, we could use some fresh air!

To the countryside, or light rain, the air is chilly. Intermittent light rain has been non-stop, the village can not see people, home are cold and cheerless, there is no children set off firecrackers. I don't know if it's because everyone in the village is trying to avoid the virus. Even though it's the 30th of this year, there's not a lot of excitement in the village. Drove to visit the sister-in-law family several relatives, greeting a few words, sent some New Year gift, we soon left. Lunch in brother-in-law home (sister's in-laws and they live together) to eat, we braved the drizzle in the vegetable field hand picked some carrots, cabbage, etc. , is a happy moment.

The country garden picks fresh vegetables in the rain

Dinner, the table pile of full dishes, there are Hubei rural unique steamed vegetables, preserved fish, fish cake, rice and other new year to eat a few dishes. Which reminds us, it's New Year's Eve. We sit close, no loud noise, no drinks, we are polite. The brother-in-law's sister-in-law smiles, repeatedly summons everybody to eat much to eat, but the atmosphere is always lively not to rise, everybody eats silently.

After dinner, before he left, he took sugarcane and orange left by himself in the countryside.

On his return to Hong Lake, he immediately went into the kitchen and began to work on the New Year's Eve dinner for his family of Eight. The rest of us should watch TV and play games.

One of my college friends in Yichang, whom I hadn't spoken to in years, was talking about me, saying, "Yichang is closed! When are you going back? Let's go if you can! " What, now? ! 30 nights? Over 30 on a Cold Day?
I shivered as I looked out at the sky that was beginning to darken.
I said, "after thirty, we'll go tomorrow. "
She never called me back. But her reminder made me nervous, and the phrase "if you can go, go" stuck in my head.

In the evening, everyone gets together to watch the Spring Festival gala. I do not know why, the lively and luxurious Spring Festival gala looks very dazzling, a bit awkward, except for a temporary addition of the recitation program let us feel the same, other, all have no taste.

25 January
New Year's Day on the 25th, eat breakfast to pack things, brother-in-law is still retain: you play two more days! As a doctor, he only has a holiday during the Spring Festival. He is very happy to have everyone back for the new year. We all shook our heads resolutely. "You'd better go, " said my sister. "You may not be able to get back later. " As the car started, I took a look at the time: 9:30. The second brother and his family also set off for Jingzhou. We were preoccupied and did not say goodbye as often as we had in previous years.

Driving away for a long time, just opened on the martial arts supervision highway, I saw a traffic police wearing a yellow warning suit, is putting some red barricades on the intersection, Florida began to close the road! There were three private cars parked at the intersection. The driver stood aside as if to discuss something with the traffic police, who shook their heads and continued to drag the obstacle into the middle of the road. GPS says the Jianli County freeway is closed, and the tollbooth at the Beluga can't get on the freeway. We didn't stop. We kept going, looking for a high-speed entrance on the provincial road.

Soon to see the message on the mobile phone, Honghu on the 25th at 10:00 AM road closure! We're only half an hour ahead of the road closures! The news took us by surprise and made us feel lucky. At the Zhujiating junction the car got on the highway and drove south.

Honghu's "closed city" message

Do not dare to stay in the service area, hurry to the bathroom, wash your hands carefully and leave. There were not many cars parked in the service area, and people were wearing masks. At noon we three people each made a bowl of noodles, in the empty service area to eat up, and quickly left. After passing through Yueyang and seeing the news, Yueyang began to close the city (road) .

Empty Changsha Service area

Nearly 7 p.m. , we arrived in Guiyang, Chenzhou, Hunan Province, where we spent most of our nights in Guangzhou. Got Off the highway and headed downtown, looking for a place to stay. Searched the nearest hotel on Qunar for more than 200 a night. I discussed with my husband that we had come from Yueyang, and that the people of Hong Lake would be afraid of us. Coming out of Hong Lake to Yueyang, which is next to each other, we wouldn't be lying if we said we were coming from Yueyang. The car stopped in front of the hotel. I got out and walked into the lobby. There was only one waitress at the front desk, and she was wearing a mask, too. When she saw me with the mask on, she looked a little alarmed and pulled back, pulling it up to the bridge of her nose.

I asked her if there was a standard room, she did not answer, but asked me: "where do you come from? "
I stuttered, "we're from Yueyang. "
"Yueyang? Can I see some ID? " She asked incredulously
I took out my husband's and my identity cards, our identity cards are Guangzhou, our license plate is Guangdong A, not e A. There's no reason for her to turn us down.
"wait a minute, I'll ask the authorities, " she said and began to talk on her cell phone, in her own dialect. She turned away so I wouldn't hear the details of the conversation. Actually, I don't understand Hunan either.
Hung up, her face visibly relaxed, and with a touch of apology, she told me, "sorry, we don't serve Yueyang. "
I wondered, "why not even the Yueyang? " 
"yesterday, on the eve of the Lunar New Year, our hotel received four guests from Hubei. Today, it was said that all guests from other places would not be received, unless they are local people, only local people can check in, " she explained

Look at her face, determined to carry out the orders of the superior, know again is useless. Well, I smiled behind my mask and turned away. I can understand her panic.

Hotels that refuse out-of-town guests (Note: from the Internet)

What about other hotels? Try again.

Sit back in the car, continue to find accommodation on the Internet, New Year's Day, Empty Room is not a lot?
The telephone contacted a very high-class hotel, the front desk is very polite, said a room, welcome to stay, one night 498 yuan. Yeah, it's kind of expensive.

And called A well-known budget hotel chain. "I'm sorry, " the hotel receptionist, Cui Shengsheng, told us. "people from other parts of the country have to go to the local community hospital for a medical check-up and a health certificate before we are allowed to check in... "

Oh, my God, what a hassle! We found it very difficult to check in, as long as it is from Hubei, it is estimated that no hotel willing to receive.
GPS says we have four hours to Guangzhou.
The husband, who had been driving for nine hours, was silent for a moment. "We're going straight back to Guangzhou, " he said. Then he started his car and headed back to the highway.
It was dark. We didn't want to talk.

A colleague who had also returned to his hometown in Hubei Province for the Lunar New Year sent me a wechat message in the afternoon asking what I was going to do. Her hometown in the countryside, originally thought the epidemic was far away from them, but the neighboring village unexpectedly appeared the family cluster disease condition. They panicked. I told her, "we're on our way back. Hurry back. When the country road is closed, YOU'LL BE IN TROUBLE! "! You follow the GPS to get out of Hubei and onto the highway."She and her husband quickly made the decision to return immediately. Looks like they're burning the midnight oil.

Night on the highway, from time to time to see Guangdong S, Guangdong B, Guangdong t, Guangdong a car passing us, heading south all the way, 20,21,22... The road has been a lot of cars. Can you imagine this is the New Year's Day Highway? There are never so many cars on the highway on the first day of the New Year! It seems that everyone is refused accommodation, or simply do not hope to stay overnight, but only to stay up all night to go home.

At some intersections, a worker in a raincoat takes the temperature of a person in a passing car. I said to the young woman taking her temperature, "thank you! Thank you for your hard work! " Her face was wet from the rain, her eyes narrowed, and she shook her head a little sheepishly. "It's all right. "

A worker at an intersection braves the rain to take a passer-by's temperature

I'm worried about my husband's energy. He keeps drinking coffee. This is the Third Cup he has brewed today. I kept talking to him to keep his head clear. "It's okay, " he consoled me. "I can hold on. "

I constantly report back through Wechat, Hong Lake, Xiaogan family has been paying attention to us, constantly in Wechat to Hubby refueling: "hold on! There are 200 kilometers! "
"Just keep gritting your teeth a little longer. There are still a hundred kilometers to go! "
"YOU'RE AWESOME! " ..
At last, near zero hour, we arrived at our destination.

The security guard on duty opened the door, we greeted each other on New Year's Day, and we gave him a red envelope.

When I got home, my body was exhausted, but my brain was still excited. Finally away from the epidemic area, the tension of the past few days slightly relaxed down. A kind of happy feeling arises spontaneously, go home really good!

January 26 to present
Since January 26th, we have been living in seclusion. While still in Hong Lake, the husband's unit had begun to investigate and monitor the situation of people returning to Hubei (he happened to be the only one to return to Hubei) , and he was required to report the temperature of a family of three to the unit every day.

One after another, my college and my children's school began to require information reporting. After the information was reported, the Neighborhood Committee and the School Neighborhood Committee in my neighborhood also called for detailed information, although it is a little annoying to be asked the same question every day by multiple management departments, we know that this is a necessary procedure for everyone's health, for our own health, we're GONNA need some serious cooperation.

Three days, five days, seven days... we've been in good shape. Alcohol, masks at home, a friend of my husband also sent us a batch of masks (we bought years ago in the pharmacy is almost out) . I am at home every day to see the report on the outbreak of mobile phone, the mood is like a roller coaster, up and down, one second furious, the next second and tears, the heart felt unbearable.

Today (February 6) , the observation time has passed 12 days. The three of us are not sick yet. I actively engage in hygiene, seriously do three meals, take temperature twice a day report. Thank so many people care about our health, the thought of giving so many people trouble, in fact, I feel very sorry.

We're two days out. We're out of quarantine. Patiently waiting for the Community Staff Home Monitoring, issued a quarantine card. However, the epidemic has not yet reached an inflection point, and our country is still facing difficulties.

Wait, I believe everything will be better!
Thanks to the author Yifan for authorizing the Conch to publish this Spring Festival on-the-spot diary. Please do not reprint it without permission. I wish the author and his family all the best. I hope the whole country can fight the epidemic soon. I will see you in the spring. The illustrations in this article are taken by the author. Exceptions are noted. There was a new announcement that the virus was contagious, but we didn't realize how serious it was, or that the vast majority of people didn't know what was going on on the 21st. My other two colleagues and their families are also on the 20th, 21st according to the plan to drive back home. On the afternoon of the 20th, we busied ourselves tidying up the house, cleaning the refrigerator, buying food and beverages, and preparing snacks such as fruit and melon seeds for the road.

It's rare to get home without traffic

On January 21, we set off at noon. The road was not so blocked as we had imagined. It was about the end of the peak of Xiaonian's homecoming. This was the first time in many years that we encountered a relatively smooth homecoming. We also felt very lucky.

Check in at 9:00 p.m. At noon on the 22nd, he arrived at the home of his sister-in-law, a surgeon at a Hong Lake Hospital, in their new one-year-old house in the neighborhood next to the hospital.

The joy of returning home was quickly diluted by the information about the epidemic online, and with all the rumors, all the data, all the wechat videos, everyone's attention was drawn to one thing: the COVID-19 epidemic is starting to spread rapidly. Panic is creeping into my heart. We lived through SARS in 2003, when I was a phd student in Beijing and the campus was closed for two months. That familiar feeling was awakened, this time, I actually in the epidemic area, this is what luck?

Unfortunately, MY SISTER-IN-LAW IS SICK! She had to welcome her brothers back home and clean up when Khan caught a cold and was hoarse and coughing! Cough, fever, that's a symptom of a COVID-19 infection. To be on the safe side, my sister followed her husband to the hospital for a checkup. After a long time did not return, everyone in the home more anxious as if the hospital is now the most dangerous place, who knows good people can be infected in the hospital? Fortunately, the test result is a bacterial infection, just take medicine to rest. The heart hanging down a little.

You follow the GPS to get out of Hubei and onto the highway."She and her husband quickly made the decision to return immediately. Looks like they're burning the midnight oil.

Night on the highway, from time to time to see Guangdong S, Guangdong B, Guangdong t, Guangdong a car passing us, heading south all the way, 20,21,22... The road has been a lot of cars. Can you imagine this is the New Year's Day Highway? There are never so many cars on the highway on the first day of the New Year! It seems that everyone is refused accommodation, or simply do not hope to stay overnight, but only to stay up all night to go home.

At some intersections, a worker in a raincoat takes the temperature of a person in a passing car. I said to the young woman taking her temperature, "thank you! Thank you for your hard work! " Her face was wet from the rain, her eyes narrowed, and she shook her head a little sheepishly. "It's all right. "

What about other hotels? Try again.

Sit back in the car, continue to find accommodation on the Internet, New Year's Day, Empty Room is not a lot?

The telephone contacted a very high-class hotel, the front desk is very polite, said a room, welcome to stay, one night 498 yuan. Yeah, it's kind of expensive.

And called A well-known budget hotel chain. "I'm sorry, " the hotel receptionist, Cui Shengsheng, told us. "people from other parts of the country have to go to the local community hospital for a medical check-up and a health certificate before we are allowed to check in... "

Oh, my God, what a hassle! We found it very difficult to check in, as long as it is from Hubei, it is estimated that no hotel willing to receive.

GPS says we have four hours to Guangzhou.

The husband, who had been driving for nine hours, was silent for a moment. "We're going straight back to Guangzhou, " he said. Then he started his car and headed back to the highway.

It was dark. We didn't want to talk.

A colleague who had also returned to his hometown in Hubei Province for the Lunar New Year sent me a wechat message in the afternoon asking what I was going to do. Her hometown in the countryside, originally thought the epidemic was far away from them, but the neighboring village unexpectedly appeared the family cluster disease condition. They panicked. I told her, "we're on our way back. Hurry back. When the country road is closed, YOU'LL BE IN TROUBLE! "! You follow the GPS to get out of Hubei and onto the highway."She and her husband quickly made the decision to return immediately. Looks like they're burning the midnight oil.

Night on the highway, from time to time to see Guangdong S, Guangdong B, Guangdong t, Guangdong a car passing us, heading south all the way, 20,21,22... The road has been a lot of cars. Can you imagine this is the New Year's Day Highway? There are never so many cars on the highway on the first day of the New Year! It seems that everyone is refused accommodation, or simply do not hope to stay overnight, but only to stay up all night to go home.

At some intersections, a worker in a raincoat takes the temperature of a person in a passing car. I said to the young woman taking her temperature, "thank you! Thank you for your hard work! " Her face was wet from the rain, her eyes narrowed, and she shook her head a little sheepishly. "It's all right. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A worker at an intersection braves the rain to take a passer-by's temperature

I'm worried about my husband's energy. He keeps drinking coffee. This is the Third Cup he has brewed today. I kept talking to him to keep his head clear. "It's okay, " he consoled me. "I can hold on. "

I constantly report back through Wechat, Hong Lake, Xiaogan family has been paying attention to us, constantly in Wechat to Hubby refueling: "hold on! There are 200 kilometers! "
"Just keep gritting your teeth a little longer. There are still a hundred kilometers to go! "
"YOU'RE AWESOME! " ..
At last, near zero hour, we arrived at our destination.

The security guard on duty opened the door, we greeted each other on New Year's Day, and we gave him a red envelope.

When I got home, my body was exhausted, but my brain was still excited. Finally away from the epidemic area, the tension of the past few days slightly relaxed down. A kind of happy feeling arises spontaneously, go home really good!

When I got home, my body was exhausted, but my brain was still excited. Finally away from the epidemic area, the tension of the past few days slightly relaxed down. A kind of happy feeling arises spontaneously, go home really good!

January 26 to present

Since January 26th, we have been living in seclusion. While still in Hong Lake, the husband's unit had begun to investigate and monitor the situation of people returning to Hubei (he happened to be the only one to return to Hubei) , and he was required to report the temperature of a family of three to the unit every day.

One after another, my college and my children's school began to require information reporting. After the information was reported, the Neighborhood Committee and the School Neighborhood Committee in my neighborhood also called for detailed information, although it is a little annoying to be asked the same question every day by multiple management departments, we know that this is a necessary procedure for everyone's health, for our own health, we're GONNA need some serious cooperation.

Three days, five days, seven days... we've been in good shape. Alcohol, masks at home, a friend of my husband also sent us a batch of masks (we bought years ago in the pharmacy is almost out) . I am at home every day to see the report on the outbreak of mobile phone, the mood is like a roller coaster, up and down, one second furious, the next second and tears, the heart felt unbearable.

Today (February 6) , the observation time has passed 12 days. The three of us are not sick yet. I actively engage in hygiene, seriously do three meals, take temperature twice a day report. Thank so many people care about our health, the thought of giving so many people trouble, in fact, I feel very sorry.

We're two days out. We're out of quarantine. Patiently waiting for the Community Staff Home Monitoring, issued a quarantine card. However, the epidemic has not yet reached an inflection point, and our country is still facing difficulties.

Wait, I believe everything will be better!
